The training images are the BBBC024 (https://bbbc.broadinstitute.org/BBBC024) data set,
where the evaluation images are the Simulated nuclei of HL60 cells stained with Hoechst.
https://celltrackingchallenge.net/3d-datasets/

List of required pip installs for all the codes 

# Core scientific / image / ML packages
pip install numpy scipy matplotlib pandas tifffile tqdm psfmodels cellpose

# PyTorch (CUDA version – recommended for your 3D U-Net training & inference)
# Change "cu124" to your installed CUDA version (11.8, 12.1, 12.4, 12.6, etc.)
pip install torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu124

# If you want CPU-only PyTorch (no GPU)
pip install torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu

# For faster data loading/visualization (optional)
pip install pillow imageio
